<br>
I don't have to give people the benefit of the doubt on this one.  If they want to make monkeys of themselves in front of me...  they're free to do so.  I will call them on it--I think that's my obligation.  I'm not calling for the term to be &quot;censored&quot;, but don't run around using it perjoratively and then cry foul when I call you on it, or cry foul when I say, &quot;Gee, I really don't feel like grouping with you again.  I think I've got some toenails to watch grow&quot;.<br>
<br>
It's not &quot;PC&quot; to challenge someone on the stuff that's coming out of their mouths.  It's just freedom of speech.  They have the right to say it, but I have the right to respond, and I have the absolute right to think poorly of someone because of the things they say.  That's life, not political correctness.<br>
<br>
The people who cry &quot;That's just 'political correctness'&quot; are often the ones who want to be able to run around and say anything <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> without consequences, without others responding to what they say, and without others thinking poorly of them because of what they say</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. <p><center><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~andersonrob/lasgalensig.jpg" border="0"></center>
<b><center>Lasgalen Lothir</center></b>
<i><center>Oakheart of the Conclave of the Righteous</center></i>
