<br>
Yeah, that's one of those things.<br>
<br>
To some people, there's a degree of empowerment that goes along with taking one of the most insulting words someone can use against you, and using it yourself as a non-insulting phrase.<br>
<br>
I personally am not fond of keeping the word in use.  I wouldn't use it myself.<br>
<br>
They would likely get insulted if you used it because there's some feeling that you have no reason to use that word.  You're not black, and thereby have no reason to throw it back in the face of your oppressors by using it, etc.<br>
