<br>
   I think the phrase &quot;Such n such is gay&quot; is offensive.  It implies that there's something wrong with being gay, and thereby something wrong with whatever they're calling gay.  I would love to go through life and never hear it again.<br>
<br>
   A lot of people use that phrase w/o giving consideration to how it could be insulting.  Between jumping on them for using an offensive phrase and calling them a homophobe, and explaining how that phrase could be read offensively and encouraging them not to use it anymore, I choose the latter (and I've seen people do the former).<br>
<br>
   &quot;Fag&quot; on the other hand is generally a direct insult.  Someone can't really use it and not know it's insulting (they're usually going for the insult).  I'd be a lot less tolerant if I heard someone using this one.<br>
<br>
   Make more sense?<br>
<br>
- Syll<br>
<br>
PS: The reasoning behind it is that I think some people are gonna change, and some people aren't.  If you're talkin to someone who has the potential of changing their behaviour to something less offensive, and you respond with something they could perceive as an attack, it puts them on the defensive and you're not gonna get anywhere.  If you give them the info they need to come to a nice conclusion, and don't go passing judgement on their personal character, they're much more likely to come to a decision about the use of that phrase that you like. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usyllestraefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syllestrae FV</A> at: 8/1/02 8:56:09 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujarkellraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JarkellRaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1048<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/1/02 9:01:43 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: That is so str8!</span><hr size=1> Thing is, maybe one person doesn't think of it as meaning anything other than stupid... but then some kid hears someone really is gay, and they think stupid, right away.  Imagine if every time someone did something stupid, you heard &quot;that's so white&quot; or something.  It'll get to you after a while.  The word is offensive.  <br>
<br>
